==English==
===Etymology===
From the way a [[duck]] puts its head down and bottom up in the air when diving underwater.
===Noun phrase===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# (''surfing'') the action of duck diving (see verb below).
===Verb phrase===
{{en-verb|duck div|ing}}

# (''surfing'') to push one's [[surfboard]] (usually a [[shortboard]]) underwater nose-first, to get the surfer and board under a [[wave]] that has [[broken]] or is just about to [[break]].
[[Category:Surfing]]
